data.description: In the heart of Atlanta, Georgia, lies the historic Carroll Heights neighborhood, seamlessly pairing suburban tranquility with urban convenience. Known for its natural beauty, this established and quiet area is neatly tucked away, featuring tree-lined streets, friendly neighbors, and a pleasantly laid-back ambience.  Despite its suburban feel, Carroll Heights offers stellar accessibility to a myriad of destinations. It sits strategically close to major highways such as I-75, I-20, and I-285, enabling residents to quickly access every corner of Atlanta, be it the heart of downtown, the bustling midtown hub, or Hartsfield-Jackson Airport. The neighborhood's excellent proximity to public transportation, including MARTA, further enhances its convenience for both commuting and local leisure pursuits.  Beyond connections to Atlanta's wider scope, Carroll Heights offers a wealth of local amenities. The community is a stone's throw from shopping, dining, and educational establishments, making day-to-day living effortlessly convenient. Rounding out Carroll Heights' charming locale, it is also situated just moments away from the Atlanta Beltline and Westside Quarry, and even closer to lovely Collier Park consisting of a recreation center, outdoor fitness stations, sports courts, and a charming nature trail.  PROPERTY QUALIFIES FOR $10,000 Grant.   Recent upgrades in 2023 include new AC coils and lines, as well as new return plumbing throughout the whole house. This residence at 626 Bolton Rd NW offers a perfect blend of comfort, modern amenities, and mature neighborhood charm.
